(4, 4, '3 Myths About Innovation (and Why Theyâ€™re Harmful)', '3-myths-about-innovation-and-why-theyre-harmful', 'http://127.0.0.1:8000/upload/blog/677c93110930d.jpg', '<p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\' id=\"isPasted\">Doing things the way they&rsquo;ve always been done is rarely the way to win new clients, gain market share, or keep employees engaged. There&rsquo;s constant pressure to innovate within the business world, whether it&rsquo;s our products, our services, or even the way we do business itself.</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>While most business leaders understand the pressure to innovate, creating a work environment that fosters continuous innovation can be difficult. For example,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hbr.org/2018/09/the-business-case-for-curiosity\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">a 2018 study revealed</a> that 70% of employees say they face barriers when asking questions at work and only 24% report regularly feeling curious in their jobs. Yet curiosity and questioning are the building blocks of innovation.</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Why is there this disparity between the desire to innovate and the implementation of innovative company culture? It all comes down to some basic misconceptions about innovation. Let&rsquo;s examine a few of these myths and why they can be so harmful to companies that care about innovating.</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Myth #1: Innovation is about producing something new&nbsp;</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>The popular definition of innovation is producing something new: a new idea, method, or device. And it&rsquo;s usually closely associated with creativity. But every story of innovation begins with a problem and the search for a solution.</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\' id=\"isPasted\">Innovation is not just about creating something new for novelty&rsquo;s sake: It needs to be rooted in a real business problem. &ldquo;Innovation involves changing your perspective on your existing resources, people, opportunities, and challenges and finding a new approach or different angle. And the result is a competitive advantage, which could be a better way to do a process, a new product, or anything that gives you an edge,&rdquo; writes&nbsp;<a href=\"https://blog.udemy.com/3-tips-for-unlocking-innovation-at-your-organization/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">Tamara Ghandour</a>, President of LaunchStreet Consultancy and Udemy instructor. &nbsp;</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Myth #2: There&rsquo;s only one way to be innovative</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>&ldquo;Every innovation strategy fails eventually,&rdquo; writes Greg Satell in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hbr.org/2017/06/the-4-types-of-innovation-and-the-problems-they-solve\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Harvard Business Review</em></a><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">,</em> &ldquo;because innovation is, at its core,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.digitaltonto.com/2017/dont-look-for-a-great-idea-look-for-a-good-problem/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">about solving problems</a> &mdash; and there are as many ways to innovate as there are types of problems to solve. There is no one true path to innovation.&rdquo;</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Satell argues that we need to treat innovation like other business disciplines. We should consider it a set of tools designed to accomplish specific objectives. We know it doesn&rsquo;t make sense to rely on a single tactic for marketing or a single source of financing. Similarly, companies should develop a portfolio of different innovation strategies for specific tasks.</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Myth #3: You&rsquo;re either innovative, or you&rsquo;re not</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>This myth is perhaps the most harmful of all because if people believe innovation is an innate skill that they don&rsquo;t possess, they&rsquo;ll never challenge themselves to develop it. Udemy instructor&nbsp;<a href=\"https://blog.udemy.com/3-tips-for-unlocking-innovation-at-your-organization/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">Tamara Ghandour</a> explains that neuroscience and behavioral psychology have disproved this myth by showing that innovation is a whole-brain experience. &ldquo;All of us have the structures for innovation,&rdquo; she writes. &ldquo;In fact, intelligence and innovation are actually two separate structures in the brain. Intelligence is similar to highways or deep grooves, while innovation has a lot of loose side roads that are connected across the brain. This tells us that everyone can innovate, and we all have the skills to do it.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>When you think of innovation as a way of problem-solving or finding solutions, it&rsquo;s much easier to break it down into its component skills &mdash; which are talents that can be developed. This include skills and capabilities like&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hbr.org/2018/09/the-business-case-for-curiosity\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">curiosity</a>, asking questions,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://blog.udemy.com/how-to-use-design-thinking-in-learning/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">design thinking</a>, and looking outside your industry for inspiration.&nbsp;</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Unlock innovation on your team&nbsp;</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>There are real business benefits to boosting innovation. The most innovative companies in the world delivered&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bcg.com/publications/2021/most-innovative-companies-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">3% more return</a> to shareholders than other large and mid-cap companies from 2005 to 2020. And as we&rsquo;ve discussed here, innovation doesn&rsquo;t have to be a mysterious superpower that&rsquo;s only available to the chosen few.&nbsp;</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Want to create a culture and develop a plan that will help you unlock innovation on your team? Download&nbsp;<a href=\"https://business.udemy.com/resources/innovative-workforce-skills/?mx_pg=blog_page_hr-and-ld&locale=en_US&ref=\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">Addressing the Skills Gaps That Hinder Innovation</a> to learn more.</p>', 'business,event,technology', '2025-01-06 20:33:59', '2025-01-06 20:36:01'),
(5, 1, 'How Managers Can Support Hybrid Workersâ€™ Well-Being', 'how-managers-can-support-hybrid-workers-well-being', 'http://127.0.0.1:8000/upload/blog/677c950fce132.webp', '<p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\' id=\"isPasted\">In the coming months, are you returning to the office, letting workers stay at home, or doing a mix of the two? If you&rsquo;re opting for the hybrid model, you&rsquo;re not alone.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mckinsey.com/business-functions/people-and-organizational-performance/our-insights/what-executives-are-saying-about-the-future-of-hybrid-work\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">Nine out of ten</a> organizations say they plan to combine remote and onsite work, confirming the concept that&nbsp;<a href=\"https://blog.udemy.com/why-future-work-hybrid/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">the future of work is hybrid</a>.</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Hybrid arrangements seem to offer the best of both worlds. Ideally, you get the deep focus that comes from working at home and the collaboration and relationship-building that come from working in the same space. But let&rsquo;s not forget that most workers are experiencing burnout at record levels. Fifty-four percent of HR leaders say their employees are fatigued from all the change they are experiencing and today&rsquo;s average employee can only absorb half as much change as previously before becoming fatigued, according to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://emtemp.gcom.cloud/ngw/globalassets/en/human-resources/documents/trends/top-priorities-for-hr-leaders-2022.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">Gartner</a>.</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>The hybrid setting can allow flexibility, but it may also contribute to isolation and burnout. Workers are still likely to feel distanced from those outside their immediate team and many of the factors that led to high levels of burnout during the earlier stages of the pandemic remain in place. Managers and business leaders who support their employees&rsquo; well-being in this new environment could help reduce burnout and improve employee retention. Let&rsquo;s explore how.&nbsp;</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Be a champion and a coach for your team</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>The profile of the ideal manager has changed along with the workplace. Yesterday&rsquo;s micro-managers and overly authoritative leaders are now a real liability and have a negative effect on employee engagement. Today&rsquo;s successful manager is more like a customer success manager: a person who makes others successful by being their champion and coach.</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>According to MIT Sloan&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/marketing.mitsmr.com/offers/ActivTrakCollection0521/MITSMR-ActivTrak-Virtual-Work-SD-0521.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Making Virtu</em>al Work a Win-Win report</a>, champions advocate for their teams and coach their people to achieve peak performance while focusing on their well-being and personal development. Both roles involve a high level of <a href=\"https://blog.udemy.com/why-emotional-intelligence-is-the-secret-to-success-at-work/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">emotional intelligence</a> and building trust, both within their teams and with external stakeholders.</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\' id=\"isPasted\">Prioritize communication</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>In a hybrid setting, clear communication is key. When there&rsquo;s no chance of running into someone in the hallway or stopping by their desk for a quick update, managers have to be intentional &mdash; and realistic &mdash; about communicating with their team.&nbsp;</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Shorter, more frequent communication tends to work better in the hybrid setting. Think Slack check-ins or 15-minute standups rather than hour-long meetings. Take advantage of asynchronous communication and set the expectation that people don&rsquo;t have to respond immediately.</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>And keep in mind that communication goes both ways. A recent&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mckinsey.com/business-functions/people-and-organizational-performance/our-insights/its-time-for-leaders-to-get-real-about-hybrid\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">report from McKinsey</a> found that &ldquo;team leaders must also follow through with sharing, listening, and hearing the needs of their team members. Without true partnership at that level, top leaders&rsquo; talk about partnering with employees is just that &mdash; talk.&rdquo;</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Don&rsquo;t reward burnout behavior</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Work-life balance is especially tricky in a hybrid setting, so managers must be extra cautious to avoid rewarding&nbsp;<a href=\"https://business.udemy.com/resources/managers-prevent-employee-burnout/?mx_pg=blog_page_hr-and-ld&locale=en_US&ref=\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">burnout behavior</a>. For example, many managers traditionally highlighted and applauded employees who made an extra effort during non-working hours. Instead, your managers should recognize long-term, quality work, and consistent performance. Successful leaders must build a sense of trust and involve the team in deciding which healthy behaviors deserve focus and promote well-being.</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Embrace empathy</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>As everyone adjusts to the changing requirements of the workplace, one of the most important skills for managers to develop is embracing empathy. Instead of maintaining rigid expectations, whether it&rsquo;s around working hours, locations, or workload, managers should strive for flexibility. It&rsquo;s critical to understand what&rsquo;s happening with each of their team members and encourage them to unplug and recharge. This is true both at the end of the day and for longer periods of time at intervals throughout the year.&nbsp;</p><h2 style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.75em; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 2.8rem; font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Support your managers &mdash; and everyone else</h2><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>The past few years have been defined by stress and burnout &mdash;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.oracle.com/a/ocom/docs/oracle-hcm-ai-at-work.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">78% of the global workforce</a> has experienced negative effects on their mental health. And as we transition into the next hybrid phase of work, your managers have a key role to play in helping support employee well-being and success.</p><p style=\'box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(28, 29, 31); font-family: \"Udemy Sans\", \"SF Pro Text\", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, \"Segoe UI\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, \"Apple Color Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Emoji\", \"Segoe UI Symbol\"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\'>Wondering what else your company can do to prioritize employees&rsquo; well-being? Download the ebook&nbsp;<a href=\"https://business.udemy.com/resources/hybrid-workplace-wellness-tips/?mx_pg=blog_page_hr-and-ld&locale=en_US&ref=\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(86, 36, 208); text-decoration: underline; transition: color 0.5s; text-underline-offset: 3px;\">How to Protect the Well-Being of Your Hybrid Workforce</a>.&nbsp;</p>', 'business,event,technology', '2025-01-06 20:40:01', '2025-01-06 20:44:31');
